obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (42642)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676&sectionId=42642&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `This Act may called the Goa, Daman and Diu Mining Concessions (Abolition and`
  line `Declaration as Mining Leases) Act, 1987.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (42643)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676&sectionId=42643&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "appointed day" means the 20th day of December, 1961;`
  line
  line `(b) "Commissioner" means the Commissioner of Payments appointed under section 8;`
  line
  line `(c) "concession holder" means a person who has been granted a mining concession;`
  line
  line `(d) "date of assent" means the date on which the assent is given by the President to this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) "Goa, Daman and Diu" means the Union territory of Goa, Daman and Diu;`
  line
  line `(f) "mines and Minerals Act" means the Mines and Minerals (Regulation and Development)`
  line `Act, 1957 (67 of 1957);`
  line
  line `(g) "mining concession" means a mining concession granted under the Portuguese Colonial`
  line `Mining Laws, 1906 (Decree of 20th September, 1906);`
  line
  line `(h) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(i) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(j) "specified date" means such date as the Central Government may, for the purpose of any`
  line `provision of this Act, by notification, specify; and different dates may be specified for different`
  line `provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(k) words and expressions used and not defined, but defined in the Mines Act, 1952 (35 of 1952)`
  line `or the Mines and Minerals Act, shall have the meanings, respectively, assigned to them in those Acts.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (42644)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Act to override all other enactments, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676&sectionId=42644&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have effect`
  line `notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any enactment (other than this Act), or any`
  line `judgment, decree or order of any court, tribunal or other authority or any instrument having effect by`
  line `virtue of any enactment other than this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (42645)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Abolition, etc., of mining concessions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676&sectionId=42645&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every mining concession specified in the First`
  line `Schedule shall, on and from the appointed day, be deemed to have been abolished, and shall, with effect`
  line `from that day, be deemed to be a mining lease granted under the Mines and Minerals Act, and the`
  line `provisions of that Act shall, save as otherwise provided in this Act, apply to such mining lease.`
  line
  line `(2) Every mining concession specified in the Second Schedule shall, on and from the day next after`
  line `the date of grant of the said concession and specified in the corresponding entry in the eighth column of`
  line `the said Schedule, be deemed to have been abolished and shall, with effect from that day, be deemed to be`
  line `a mining lease granted under the Mines and Minerals Act, and the provisions of that Act shall, save as`
  line `otherwise provided in this Act, apply to such mining lease.`
  line
  line `(3) If, after the date of assent, the Central Government is satisfied, whether from any information`
  line `received by it or otherwise, that there has been any error, omission or misdescription in relation to the`
  line `particulars of any mining concession or the name and residence of any concession holder specified in the`
  line `First or the Second Schedule, it may, by notification, correct such error, omission or misdescription, and`
  line `on the issue of such notification, the First or the Second Schedule, as the case may be, shall be deemed to`
  line `have been amended accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (42646)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `General effect of declaring the mining concessions to be mining leases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676&sectionId=42646&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a mining`
  line `concession has been deemed to be a mining lease under section 4, the concession holder shall, on and`
  line `from the day mentioned in that section, be deemed to have become the holder of such mining lease under`
  line `the Mines and Minerals Act in relation to the mine to which the mining concession relates, subject to the`
  line `condition that the period of such lease shall, notwithstanding anything contained in that Act, extend up to`
  line `a period of six months from the date of assent.`
  line
  line `(2) On the expiry of the period of any mining lease under sub-section (1), it may, if so desired by the`
  line `holder of such lease and on an application being made by him in accordance with the provisions of the`
  line `Mines and Minerals Act and the rules made thereunder, be renewed on such terms and conditions, and up`
  line `to the maximum period for which, such lease can be renewed under the provisions of that Act and the`
  line `rules made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (42647)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Payment of amounts to concession holders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676&sectionId=42647&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Every concession holder specified in the second`
  line `column of the First and the Second Schedules shall be given by the Central Government, in cash, and in`
  line `the manner specified in Chapter IV, for the abolition of the mining concessions held by him, and`
  line `declaring it as a mining lease, under section 4, an amount equal to the amount specified against him in the`
  line `corresponding entry in the eighth column of the First Schedule and the ninth column of the Second`
  line `Schedule, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (42648)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Payment of further amount.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676&sectionId=42648&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall also be given by the Central Government, in cash,`
  line `to every concession holder specified in the second column of the First and the Second Schedules, simple`
  line `interest at the rate of four per cent. per annum on the amount specified against such concession holder in`
  line `the corresponding entry in the eighth column of the First Schedule and the ninth column of the Second`
  line `Schedule, as the case may be, for the period commencing on the date of assent and ending on the date of`
  line `payment of such amount to the Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(2) The amount referred to in sub-section (1) shall be in addition to the amount specified in the First`
  line `Schedule or the Second Schedule, as the case may be`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (42649)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Commissioner of Payments to be appointed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676&sectionId=42649&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of disbursing the amounts`
  line `payable to the concession holders under this Act, the Central Government shall appoint such person as it`
  line `may think fit to be the Commissioner of Payments.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may appoint such other persons as it may think fit to assist the`
  line `Commissioner and thereupon the Commissioner may authorise one or more of such persons also to`
  line `exercise all or any of the powers exercisable by him under this Act and different persons may be`
  line `authorised to exercise different powers.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person authorised by the Commissioner to exercise any of the powers exercisable by the`
  line `Commissioner may exercise those powers in the same manner and with the same effect as if they have`
  line `been conferred, on that person directly by this Act and not by way of authorisation.`
  line
  line `(4) The salaries and allowances of the Commissioner and other persons appointed under this section`
  line `shall be defrayed out of the Consolidated Fund of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (42650)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Payment by the Central Government to the Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676&sectionId=42650&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government`
  line `shall, within thirty days from the specified date, pay, in cash, to the Commissioner, for payment to the`
  line `concession holders, a sum equal to the sum specified against the mining concessions in the First and the`
  line `Second Schedules, together with the amount of interest referred to in section 7.`
  line
  line `(2) A deposit account shall be opened by the Central Government, in favour of the Commissioner, in`
  line `the Public Account of India, and every amount paid under this Act to the Commissioner shall be`
  line `deposited by him to the credit of the said deposit account and the said deposit account shall be operated`
  line `by the Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(3) Records shall be maintained by the Commissioner in respect of each of the concession holder in`
  line `relation to which payments have been made to him under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) Interest accruing on the amount standing to the credit of the deposit account referred to in`
  line `sub-section (2) shall enure to the benefit of the concession holders.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (42651)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Claims to be made to the Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676&sectionId=42651&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every concession holder, having a claim for the`
  line `payment of the amount referred to in section 6, shall prefer such claim before the Commissioner within`
  line `thirty days from the specified date:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Commissioner is satisfied that the claimant was prevented by sufficient cause`
  line `from preferring the claim within the said period of thirty days, he may entertain the claim within a further`
  line `period of thirty days, but not thereafter.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner shall fix a certain date on or before which every claimant shall file the proof of`
  line `his claim.`
  line
  line `(3) Not less than fourteen days notice of the date so fixed shall be given by advertisement in one`
  line `issue of the daily newspaper in the English language and one issue of any daily newspaper in the regional`
  line `language as the Commissioner may consider suitable, and every such notice shall call upon the claimant`
  line `to file the proof of his claim with the Commissioner within the time specified in the advertisement.`
  line
  line `(4) Every claimant, who fails to file the proof of his claim within the time specified by the`
  line `Commissioner, shall be excluded from the disbursement made by the Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(5) The Commissioner shall, after such investigation as may, in his opinion, be necessary and after`
  line `giving the concession holder, a reasonable opportunity of being heard, by order in writing admit or reject`
  line `the claim in whole or in part.`
  line
  line `(6) The Commissioner shall have the power to regulate his own procedure in all matters arising out of`
  line `the discharge of his functions, including the place or places at which he will hold his sittings and shall, for the purpose of making any investigation under this Act, have the same powers as are vested in a civil`
  line `court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), while trying a suit in respect of the following`
  line `matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the summoning and enforcing the attendance of any witness and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) the discovery and production of any document or other material object producible as`
  line evidence;
  line
  line `(c) the reception of evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) the issuing of any commission for the examination of any witnesses.`
  line
  line `(7) Any investigation before the Commissioner shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within the`
  line `meaning of sections 193 and 228 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) and the Commissioner shall be`
  line `deemed to be a civil court for the purposes of section 195 and Chapter XXVI of the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  line
  line `(8) A claimant, who is dissatisfied with the decision of the Commissioner, may prefer an appeal`
  line `against the decision to the principal civil court of original jurisdiction within the local limits of whose`
  line `jurisdiction the relevant mine is situated.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (42652)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Liability of Central Government to end on payment of claim.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676&sectionId=42652&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `After admitting a claim under`
  line `this Act, the amount due in respect of such claim shall be paid by the Commissioner to the person or`
  line `persons to whom such amount is due, and, on such payment, the liability of the Central Government in`
  line `respect of such claim shall stand discharged.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (42653)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Disputes how to be dealt with.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676&sectionId=42653&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `In the event of there being a doubt or dispute as to the right of a`
  line `person to receive the whole or any part of the amount referred to in section 6 or section 7, the`
  line `Commissioner shall refer the matter to the court for a decision, and shall make the disbursement in`
  line `accordance with the decision of the court.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section "court", in relation to a mining concession, means the principal civil`
  line `court of original jurisdiction within the local limits of whose jurisdiction the mines relating to such`
  line `concession is situated.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (42654)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Undisbursed or unclaimed amount to be deposited to the general revenue account.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676&sectionId=42654&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line Any
  line `money paid to the Commissioner which remains undisbursed or unclaimed after such payment for a`
  line `period of three years shall be transferred by the Commissioner to the general revenue account of the`
  line `Central Government; but a claim to any money transferred may be preferred to the Central Government`
  line `by the concession holder entitled to such payment and shall be dealt with as if such transfer had not been`
  line `made, the order, if any, for the payment of the claim being treated as an order for the refund of revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (42663)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title Repealed.
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676&sectionId=42663&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `[Amendment of Act 67 of 1957.]--Rep. by Repealing and Amending Act, 2001 (30 of 2001), s.2`
  line `and The First Schedule (w.e.f. 3-9-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (42664)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676&sectionId=42664&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `Any person who contravenes the provisions of this Act shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years or with fine which may extend to two thousand`
  line `rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (42656)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676&sectionId=42656&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who at the time the offence was committed was in charge of, and was responsible`
  line `to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company as well as the company, shall be deemed`
  line `to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he had exercised`
  line `all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall be deemed to be guilty of`
  line `that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (42657)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676&sectionId=42657&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding`
  line `shall lie against the Central Government or any officer or other employee of that Government, or any`
  line `person authorised by that Government for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done`
  line `under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against the Central Government or any officer or other`
  line `employee of that Government or any person authorised by that Government for any damage caused or`
  line `likely to be caused by anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (42658)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676&sectionId=42658&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, direct that all or any`
  line `of the powers exercisable by it under this Act, other than the powers conferred by sections 20 and 21,may`
  line `also be exercised by such person or persons as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) Whenever any delegation of power is made under sub-section (1), the person to whom such power`
  line `has been delegated shall act under the direction, control and supervision of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (42659)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Declaration as to the policy of the State.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676&sectionId=42659&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `It is hereby declared that this Act is for giving effect`
  line `to the policy of the State towards securing the principles specified in clauses (b) and (c) of Article 39 of`
  line `the Constitution.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section, "State" has the same meaning as in Article 12 of the Constitution.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (42660)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676&sectionId=42660&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, make rules to carry`
  line `out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (42661)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676&sectionId=42661&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, the Central Government may, by order, not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, remove the`
  line `difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of two years from the date of`
  line assent.
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (42662)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title Validation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676&sectionId=42662&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_00001_198716_1517807317676
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything in any other law for the time being in force or any`
  line `judgment, decree or order of any court, tribunal or other authority,--`
  line
  line `(a) every concession holder shall, for the period commencing on and from the date when his`
  line `mining concession had been declared to be a mining lease and ending with the date of expiry of the`
  line `period of his lease under the provisions of this Act (hereafter in this section referred to as the said`
  line `period), be liable to pay the dead rent or, as the case may be, royalty, due in respect of such lease`
  line `under the provisions of the Mines and Minerals Act and the rules made thereunder, and such amount`
  line `shall, save as otherwise provided in this section, be recoverable from him;`
  line
  line `(b) any amount paid by the concession holder for the said period, either as a fixed tax or as a`
  line `proportional tax, or both, or as a royalty under protest shall be deemed to have been dead rent or, as`
  line `the case may be, royalty, paid in accordance with law and such amounts shall not be liable to be`
  line `refunded; and`
  line
  line `(c) due credit of all such amounts paid by a concession holder under clause (b) shall be given to`
  line `him in determining the dead rent or, as the case may be, royalty payable by him under clause (a), as if`
  line `this Act and the Mines and Minerals Act and the rules made thereunder had been in force at all`
  line `material times, and accordingly--`
  line
  line `(i) no suit or other proceeding shall be instituted, maintained or continued in any court or`
  line `other authority against the Government or any person or authority whatsoever for the refund of`
  line `any amounts paid by a concession holder under clause (b); and`
  line
  line `(ii) no court shall enforce any decree or order directing the refund of any amounts so paid, on`
  line `the ground that the mining concession is not a mining lease.`
  line
  line `(2) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that nothing in sub-section (1) shall be construed`
  line `as preventing any person,--`
  line
  line `(a) from questioning, in accordance with the provisions of the Mines and Minerals Act and the`
  line `rules made thereunder, the assessment of any dead rent or royalty for the said period; or`
  line
  line `(b) from claiming refund of any dead rent or royalty paid by him in excess of the amount due`
  line `from him under the Mines and Minerals Act and the rules made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
